SOURCE_NOTE: Infant mortality rate is the number of infants dying before reaching one year of age, per 1,000 live births in a given year.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: Estimates Developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org. Projected data are from the United Nations Population Division's World Population Prospects; and may in some cases not be consistent with data before the current year.
